BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a2fb4c192358590d@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T133000Z
DTEND:20260611T141500Z
SUMMARY:NewDad
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Irish indie rock phenoms\n\nKids are rummaging parents’ music
  collections\, and subsequently starting cool new bands. You can add Irish
  indie rockers NewDad to that crop.Those tried and true sounds clashing he
 ad on with restless\, radical youth makes for something unspeakbly fresh. 
 NewDad's gloomy but playful concoction of grunge\, shoegaze and dream pop 
 is likewise brimming with brilliant melodies and a lightning-in-the bottle
  energy that's hard to match.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-7da35ab9d90e468f@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T151500Z
DTEND:20260611T161500Z
SUMMARY:Sudan Archives
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Gadget girl of forward-thinking pop\, dance and R&B\n\nEvery ti
 me Sudan Archives releases a new album\, it feels like we’re shown a gli
 mpse into the future of pop music itself.\nSudan’s latest long player TH
 E BPM ups the tempo from her pop\, R&B and hip-hop abstractions\, taking d
 eep inspiration from the legendary club scenes in Detroit\, New Jersey and
  Chicago. A quest to get in sync with her inner rhythm: somewhere between 
 the spiritual and the silly\, cherrypicking elements from the gospel as re
 adily as from cyberpunk.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-8ade04d055bc65da@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T171500Z
DTEND:20260611T181500Z
SUMMARY:Amaarae
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Transatlantic R&B & pop marvel\n\nAmaarae is a self-proclaimed 
 warrior princess of radical dancefloor bangers.\nBorn in the Bronx with Gh
 anaian roots\, this fast-rising producer\, songwriter and vocalist pens sw
 eltering tracks that are both ethereal and club-ready. Amaarae's transatla
 ntic R&B/Afrobeat hybrid pop is rooted in highlife\, baile funk and dance 
 music\, yet bares a non-conformist\, playful streak that trail blazes stra
 ight into the future.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9c5cb036e6d3d2e4@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T191500Z
DTEND:20260611T201500Z
SUMMARY:Blood Incantation
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:One of death metal's most visionary bands\n\nIn their own words
 \, death metal behemoths Blood Incantation make mystical music for mystica
 l people.\nAnd for brevity's sake\, this is all true. For these guys are a
 ctual wizards in real life\, fusing elements like psychedelic rock\, black
  metal\, sci-fi\, ambient\, and prog into something\, well\, unlike anythi
 ng else. Weird? Transcendental? Influential to a whole new generation of m
 etal bands? Blood Incantation checks off all those boxes and then some. Th
 is will be no mere concert: this will be an odyssey of the gravest kind.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d98008bc3c383ca5@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T220000Z
DTEND:20260611T230000Z
SUMMARY:Mula
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Narco pop superstar\n\nMula and his intoxicating genre-blending
  narco pop blueprint are changing the entire Dutch rap game.If you walk th
 e streets at night in any city\, you hear all sorts of music fading in and
  out of each other – indie\, pop\, psychedelic rock\, rap\, reggaeton. M
 ula adopted this miscellany to his own kitchen sink hip-hop tales and kabo
 om\, suddenly\, he became one of the most revitalising performers of the L
 ow Countries. And we’re sure glad to have Mula back in Hilvarenbeek.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f8beb43b47497f38@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T100000Z
DTEND:20260612T104500Z
SUMMARY:mark william lewis
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Resonant & cinematic alternative folk\n\nWithin the dusky\, noc
 turnal songs of mark william lewis you can untangle head and heart at your
  own desired pace.Blessed with a deep baritone and a talent for painting s
 cenes with through minimal means\, it’s no wonder art house film giant A
 24 decided to ink the UK songwriter to a record deal. There is a gothic my
 stery lingering in lewis's songs\, a love for electronic music\, rap\, gri
 me and indie rock permeating through. An artist whose romanticism and flui
 dity are understated\, yet undeniably magnetic.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-3218e20c10ad7dd6@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T111500Z
DTEND:20260612T120000Z
SUMMARY:Hiqpy
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Hot-blooded shoegaze/alt-rock sensation\n\nAt a blazing pace\, 
 Amsterdam quartet Hiqpy has already mastered all the intangibles of a grea
 t rock band.\nThe band has cultivated a penchant for scene stealing stage 
 dramatics and scorching melodies\, executed with more bluster and charisma
  than you can throw a stick at. With long awaited debut LP Slow Death Of A
  Good Girl unleashed in the world\, Hiqpy are ready to up the ante for the
 ir second Best Kept Secret-stint.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-2e45f0a0f982b534@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T124500Z
DTEND:20260612T134500Z
SUMMARY:Weval (live)
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Tasteful electro-acoustic dream weavers\n\nThere's an immense c
 are this Dutch duo put into their chosen craft – and a surrender to one
 ’s deepest listening instincts.Those two methods are part of the Weval m
 agic – the studious tinkering vs. the spontaneity of live instrumentatio
 n\, until that sweet innuendo between the artificial and the organic is ac
 hieved. Through headphones and across the dancefloors\, Weval remains an e
 ver-sublime and satisfying operation\, renowned across all corners of the 
 world.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-0cfe250eaaa4f302@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T144500Z
DTEND:20260612T154500Z
SUMMARY:Aldous Harding
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Chameleon-like alt folk siren\n\nAldous Harding is one of those
  rare shapeshifting artists that comes along every so often.Sometimes in t
 he very same song\, she can be theatrical\, comedic\, soothing and frighte
 ning in a heartbeat – leaving audiences catching their breath on what co
 uld happen next. Since Harding's 2019 breakthrough album Designer\, her my
 stique and magnetism only seems to have grown\, writing songs that often c
 apture the phenomena inside the gaps of living we tend to overlook.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a27f4b671fdddf11@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T164500Z
DTEND:20260612T174500Z
SUMMARY:Nation of Language
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:New York synth pop torchbearers\n\nAfter Kraftwerk\, New Order\
 , and LCD Soundsystem passed the baton\, now Nation Of Language upholds th
 e continuum of new wave and synth pop greatness.The New York band's latest
  LP Dance Called Memory\, poetically enough\, grasps retroactively with ho
 w one wishes to be remembered\, its songs emphasising physicality\, imperm
 anence and flaw over artifice and perfection. We're pleased to bring Natio
 n Of Language back to Best Kept Secret's lakeside scenery.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-fec3b6d43327ff83@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T184500Z
DTEND:20260612T194500Z
SUMMARY:Tramhaus
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Rotterdam-based punk rock collossus\n\nAt a blistering pace\, T
 ramhaus snowballed from Rotterdam’s latest post-punk curiosity to one of
  Europe’s greatest rock bands.And with two legendary shows at Best Kept 
 Secret already under the group's belt\, it makes perfect sense to invite t
 hem back for another noisy merry-go-round. Beneath all those powerhouse ri
 ffs\, blunt force trauma\, and indefatigable DIY spirit\, Tramhaus are a b
 and with a big beating heart\, and a special knack for making audiences fe
 el present\, seen and loved.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5e6587a744c7c1e2@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T220000Z
DTEND:20260612T230000Z
SUMMARY:Job Jobse
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Amsterdam's most notorious club culture omnivore\n\nFrom gravey
 ard shifts at legendary club Trouw to becoming one of the most renowned DJ
 s worldwide\, Job Jobse’s life is a metronome-driven pipe dream.\nThroug
 h all of his dizzying success\, Jobse's love for the game and the geeking 
 out behind the booth never ever wavers. The reason why this guy is so in-d
 emand is obvious: Job can do any type of DJ set that fits the imagination\
 , from euphoria bursting trance to slow-building house beats.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-ca489e0904a7cc78@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T100000Z
DTEND:20260613T104500Z
SUMMARY:∑tella
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Captivating Mediterranean dream pop\n\nIn Greek songwriter Σte
 lla’s music\, you can literally smell the sea air and the dizzy spells o
 f unspoken attraction.\nHer sultry\, crisply arranged tunes inspire you to
  take a breather from life’s familiar strains\, through the prism of the
  quirky\, vibrant synth-pop of debut LP ‘The Break’ or the more cinema
 tic seaside scenes of ‘Up And Away’. With the latter\, Σtella achieve
 d the milestone of being the first Greek artist to be signed by legendary 
 indie label Sub Pop.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-32d08178d2f58384@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T111500Z
DTEND:20260613T121500Z
SUMMARY:WIES
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Expressive & eclectic Dutch alt-pop\n\nWith an uncanny talent f
 or turning any subject into song\, WIES became one of the most beloved mod
 ern bands in Dutch pop.\nThe group's steady growth hasn’t come at the co
 st of expressing the nuances and finer observations in the obstacle course
  that’s life. The passage of time\, the growing pains\, the hopes and fe
 ars - indeed\, no corners are cut once the curtains open for WIES at Best 
 Kept Secret. And we’re happy to see them return.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5b7bcbc728f6fb47@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T130000Z
DTEND:20260613T134500Z
SUMMARY:Sophie Straat
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Dutch protest singer extraordinaire\n\nSophie Straat feels just
  as much at home on prime time TV as at some grubby grassroots venue\, whi
 ch is very telling about how broadly her work resonates.\nThe Amsterdam-ba
 sed protest singer is a savvy satirist who possesses immense talent for ad
 dressing the ills of the world with maximum entertainment. Stylistically\,
  she veers from Dutch smartlap folk to punk rock on a whim – often with 
 message attached. All-embracing and eternally on the frontlines against in
 justice\, Sophie Straat is one of the most unique and outspoken voices in 
 Dutch pop.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-e30db2166f8c72c1@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T144500Z
DTEND:20260613T154500Z
SUMMARY:Don West
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Aussie soul hunk with vintage sound\n\nIn the immortal words of
  Arthur Conley: ‘Do you like good music/ That sweet soul music?’ Austr
 alian singer Don West certainly does.\nSo much so even that West has adopt
 ed his own “coastal” version of that vintage soul lineage: the kind th
 at makes you want to chill beachside with a good book\, or ride a wave or 
 two when the wind’s just right. Obviously\, somewhere in the bedroom wou
 ld also suffice. If West’s honeysweet croon doesn’t take you out immed
 iately\, his striking charisma certainly will.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9a851979072ecb0e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T164500Z
DTEND:20260613T174500Z
SUMMARY:Yard Act
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Dry-witted post-punk dissidents\n\nFrom boy bands\, cowbell dis
 co to MacBeth\, nothing is excluded in the wonderfully witty pocket world 
 of Yard Act.Initially breaking in the post-punk revival's slipstream\, Yar
 d Act quickly separated themselves from the pack of soapbox-shouters with 
 their charmingly flawed character sketches\, offbeat everyman humor and st
 arry-eyed pop sensibility. On their latest LP Where's My Utopia? Yard Act 
 remain as sincere as they are endlessly entertaining.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-8e4493b69e1b5579@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T184500Z
DTEND:20260613T194500Z
SUMMARY:Joey Valence & Brae
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Energetic retro-rap jams\n\nViral sensation and rap duo Joey Va
 lence & Brae are the answer to the question: what if the Beastie Boys had 
 been Gen Zers?\nJoey Valence & Brae's tracks are jam packed with nerdy ref
 erences to pop culture\, memes\, and games. They perform that sweet sample
 -based old-skool rap style with the almost endless possibilities of today.
  For example\, the two childhood friends shot the video for Punk Tactics e
 ntirely on a Nintendo DS. Such fun stunts have earned Joey Valence & Brae 
 a legion of millions of fans.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f25db4ed12255bc3@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T213000Z
DTEND:20260613T223000Z
SUMMARY:Sammy Virji
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Spry UK Garage-reigniter\n\nSammy Virji has quickly made his ma
 rk on the scene and established himself as a pioneer of the UKG renaissanc
 e.\nOver the past eight years\, he's expanded his discography and created 
 an unforgettable live show. After his iconic single "Shella Verse" featuri
 ng Flowdan and his viral DJ Mag stream\, he's become an indispensable part
  of the dance world. With his new album\, "If U Need It\," he's steadily g
 rowing his fan base. Sammy is bringing UKG to a wider audience while simul
 taneously developing and refining his own sound.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
